<!-- gsd-conventions-start source:CONVENTIONS.md -->
## Conventions

## Language & Runtime
## Naming Patterns
- PascalCase for file names: `Code.gs`, `Transacoes.gs`, `Dashboard.gs`, `Configuracoes.gs`, `Setup.gs`, `Gemini.gs`, `Utils.gs`
- Each file corresponds to a domain module (transactions, dashboard, config, AI, setup, utilities)
- File header: JSDoc block comment with `/** ... */` describing the file's purpose
- PascalCase: `WebApp.html`, `Sidebar.html`, `ComprovanteSidebar.html`, `ConfiguracoesUI.html`, `Relatorio.html`
- Single-file architecture: `<style>`, `<html>`, `<script>` all in one file вЂ” no external dependencies except Chart.js CDN
- camelCase for all functions: `salvarTransacao()`, `gerarProximoId()`, `obterResumoMensal()`
- Prefixed underscore for private/internal helpers: `_normDescDup()`, `_descSimilarDup()`, `_repararArrayTruncado()`, `_configDefaults()`
- Portuguese naming throughout вЂ” verbs in infinitive form: `listar`, `salvar`, `obter`, `atualizar`, `criar`, `excluir`, `gerar`, `compilar`
- CRUD verbs: `salvar*` (create/update), `editar*` (update), `excluir*` (delete), `listar*` / `get*` (read), `obter*` (fetch/compute)
- Getter shortcuts use `get` prefix: `getConfig()`, `getTodasConfigs()`, `getPessoa1Nome()`, `getCategoriasList()`
- Short abbreviated names in WebApp: `al()` (alert), `fmt()` (format currency), `cAnalisar()` (comprovante analyze), `ppSalvar()` (poupanГ§a save)
- Section prefixes: `c*` for comprovante, `r*` for relatГіrio, `pp*` for poupanГ§a, `cfg*` for configuraГ§Гµes, `cf*` for fatura
- Sidebars use clearer names: `salvar()`, `selPessoa()`, `selTipo()`, `carregarCats()`
- camelCase: `totalReceitas`, `pessoaNome`, `dataTransacao`, `valorAbs`
- Short aliases for spreadsheet objects: `ss` (spreadsheet), `sh` (sheet), `sh0` (sheet reference in batch ops)
- Single-letter loop vars: `l` (line counter in Dashboard), `i`, `j`, `r` (row), `c` (column)
- Config keys use snake_case strings: `'nome_pessoa1'`, `'salario_pessoa2'`, `'dia_fechamento_fatura'`
- UPPER_SNAKE_CASE: `SHEETS_NAMES`, `COL`, `MES_NOMES`, `GEMINI_URL`, `METODOS_PADRAO`
- Declared with `const` at file top level in `Code.gs`
- No TypeScript вЂ” plain JS objects used as enum-like constants (`SHEETS_NAMES`, `COL`)
## Code Style
- No automated formatter (Prettier, ESLint) configured
- 2-space indentation in `.gs` files
- Minified/compressed CSS in HTML files (single-line declarations)
- Semicolons used consistently in `.gs` files
- Template literals used in `const`/`let` blocks, string concatenation with `+` in `var` blocks
- `const` and `let` preferred in newer/main logic (`Code.gs`, `Dashboard.gs`, main functions in `Transacoes.gs`)
- `var` used in batch operations and compatibility-critical code (`salvarMultiplasTransacoes`, `Configuracoes.gs` internal functions, `_repararArrayTruncado`)
- Mixed `const`/`var` within some files вЂ” `var` appears in functions that iterate or need hoisting
- No enforced limit вЂ” some lines exceed 200+ characters, especially prompt strings in `Gemini.gs` and inline CSS
- No `.eslintrc`, `.prettierrc`, or any linting config present
- No `package.json` вЂ” this is a pure GAS project with no npm/node tooling
## Import Organization
- Constants declared in `Code.gs` (`SHEETS_NAMES`, `COL`, `MES_NOMES`) are accessible everywhere
- Functions from any `.gs` file can call functions from any other `.gs` file
- Order of file loading is non-deterministic вЂ” avoid redeclaring `const`/`let` across files
- `var METODOS_PADRAO` in `Configuracoes.gs` uses `var` specifically to avoid redeclaration errors
- No module imports вЂ” all JS is inline `<script>` blocks
- Chart.js loaded via CDN: `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@4.4.7`
- Communication with backend via `google.script.run` API
## Error Handling
- `sucesso: boolean` вЂ” always present in result objects
- `mensagem: string` вЂ” human-readable message with emoji prefix (`вњ…`, `вќЊ`, `вљ пёЏ`)
- `codigo: string` вЂ” optional error code for programmatic handling (e.g., `'DUPLICATA'`)
- Additional data fields vary by function: `id`, `dados`, `itens`, `existentes`, `duplicatas`
- Dashboard update failures are swallowed: `try { atualizarDashboard(); } catch (e) { /* silencioso */ }`
- Salary config updates swallowed: `try { setConfig(...); } catch (e2) { /* silencioso */ }`
- Empty `catch (_) {}` blocks in batch operations (`salvarMultiplasTransacoes`)
- `Logger.log()` with context tag: `Logger.log('[functionName] ' + e.message)`
- `logErro(contexto, e)` utility in `Utils.gs` for structured error logging with stack trace
- Pattern: `[ERRO] context: message\nstack`
- `google.script.run.withFailureHandler(fn)` catches server errors
- Alert helper `al(prefix, message, type)` displays colored alerts (`'s'` success, `'e'` error, `'w'` warning, `'i'` info)
- Auto-dismiss alerts after 6 seconds (except `'i'` type)
## Return Value Patterns
- `listarTransacoes(filtros)` в†’ `Array<Object>` or `[]`
- `getTodasConfigs()` в†’ config object (never null вЂ” falls back to `_configDefaults()`)
- `getConfig(chave)` в†’ value or `null`
- `salvarTransacao(dados)` в†’ `{ sucesso, mensagem, id? }`
- `editarTransacao(dados)` в†’ `{ sucesso, mensagem }`
- `excluirTransacao(id)` в†’ `{ sucesso, mensagem }`
- `analisarComprovante(...)` в†’ `{ sucesso, dados?, itens?, multiplo?, mensagem }`
- `chamarGeminiAPI(...)` в†’ `{ sucesso, texto?, truncado?, mensagem }`
## Spreadsheet Access Patterns
## CSS / Frontend Conventions
- `.alert` with modifiers `.s` (success), `.e` (error), `.w` (warning)
- `.btn`, `.btn-p` (primary), `.btn-sec` (secondary), `.btn-ia` (AI purple), `.btn-save`
- `.card` with modifiers `.g` (green), `.r` (red), `.b` (blue), `.o` (orange)
- `.fg` (form group), `.row` (flex row), `.panel`, `.sec` (section)
- `.spin` (CSS-only loading spinner animation)
## Comments
- File-level JSDoc header describing file purpose: `/** Transacoes.gs вЂ” CRUD de transaГ§Гµes financeiras */`
- Section separators using ASCII art: `// в•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ`, `// в”Ђв”Ђ Section Title в”Ђв”Ђ`
- Inline comments for non-obvious business logic (credit card billing cycle, salary deduplication)
- JSDoc `@param` used sparingly: only on `verificarDuplicataTransacao` for the cache parameter
## Function Design
- Single object parameter for complex inputs: `salvarTransacao(dados)`, `editarTransacao(dados)`, `listarTransacoes(filtros)`
- Positional params for simple lookups: `getConfig(chave)`, `atualizarPerfil(numero)`, `excluirTransacao(id)`
- Optional params with defaults: `filtros = filtros || {}`, `dados = dados || {}`
- Internal cache parameters prefixed with `__`: `dados.__linhasDupCache`, `dados.__idPreAlocado`
- Always return something вЂ” never `void` for functions called from frontend
- Fallback returns on error: `return []`, `return null`, `return { sucesso: false, ... }`
## Module Design
- `Code.gs` вЂ” globals, entry points (`doGet`, `onOpen`), UI navigation
- `Setup.gs` вЂ” one-time initialization, sheet creation
- `Configuracoes.gs` вЂ” configuration CRUD, category/payment method management, initial data loading
- `Transacoes.gs` вЂ” transaction CRUD, budget, savings (poupanГ§a), monthly reports
- `Dashboard.gs` вЂ” spreadsheet dashboard rendering
- `Gemini.gs` вЂ” all AI integration (receipt analysis, insights, category suggestion, API calls)
- `Utils.gs` вЂ” shared utilities (formatting, date, logging)
- `WebApp.html` вЂ” main standalone app (2119 lines, 7 tabs, full SPA)
- `Sidebar.html`, `ComprovanteSidebar.html`, `Relatorio.html`, `ConfiguracoesUI.html` вЂ” legacy sidebar versions
