<!-- gsd-architecture-start source:ARCHITECTURE.md -->
## Architecture

## Pattern Overview
- Flat-file server-side codebase (`.gs` files) running on Google Apps Script V8 runtime
- Client-side HTML/CSS/JS served via `HtmlService` (sidebars + standalone Web App)
- Communication between client and server exclusively via `google.script.run` async bridge
- Google Sheets tabs used as relational-like data tables (no external database)
- Dual access mode: embedded in Google Sheets (menu + sidebars) and standalone Web App (`doGet`)
- External AI integration with Google Gemini API via `UrlFetchApp`
## Layers
- Purpose: Application bootstrap, menu creation, sidebar launchers, Web App endpoint
- Location: `Code.gs`
- Contains: `doGet()` (Web App entry), `onOpen()` (Sheets menu), sidebar opener functions, `inicializarPlanilha()`, global constants (`SHEETS_NAMES`, `COL`, `MES_NOMES`)
- Depends on: All other `.gs` files (calls functions from each)
- Used by: Google Apps Script runtime (triggers), HTML clients (via `google.script.run`)
- Purpose: Read/write key-value configuration from the `вљ™пёЏ Config` sheet tab; provide initial data payload to HTML clients
- Location: `Configuracoes.gs`
- Contains: `getConfig()`, `setConfig()`, `getTodasConfigs()`, `salvarConfiguracoes()`, `getCategoriasList()`, `getDadosIniciais()`, `getMesesDisponiveis()`, `getMetodosPagamento()`, `salvarMetodosPagamento()`, `getOrcamentos()`, `salvarOrcamentos()`
- Depends on: `Code.gs` (constants `SHEETS_NAMES`, `COL`)
- Used by: Every other `.gs` file and all HTML clients
- Purpose: Full CRUD for financial transactions, savings (poupanГ§a), budget comparison, monthly reports
- Location: `Transacoes.gs`
- Contains: `salvarTransacao()`, `salvarMultiplasTransacoes()`, `editarTransacao()`, `excluirTransacao()`, `excluirMultiplasTransacoes()`, `listarTransacoes()`, `compilarResumoTransacoes()`, `calcularRendaExibida()`, `obterResumoMensal()`, `getOrcamentoVsRealizado()`, `gerarPayloadRelatorioMensal()`, savings CRUD (`getPoupanca()`, `salvarPoupanca()`, `excluirPoupanca()`, `getSaldoPoupanca()`), salary reference management (`upsertSalarioDoMes()`, `obterSalarioReferenciaMensal()`), duplicate detection (`verificarDuplicataTransacao()`)
- Depends on: `Configuracoes.gs` (`getConfig`, `getTodasConfigs`, `setConfig`), `Code.gs` (constants), `Dashboard.gs` (`atualizarDashboard`)
- Used by: `Dashboard.gs`, `Gemini.gs`, all HTML clients
- Purpose: Programmatically write formatted data directly into Google Sheets tabs (Dashboard, Profile, Joint Analysis)
- Location: `Dashboard.gs`
- Contains: `atualizarDashboard()`, `atualizarPerfil()`, `atualizarAnaliseConjunta()`, `escreverSecao()` helper
- Depends on: `Transacoes.gs` (data retrieval), `Configuracoes.gs` (config), `Code.gs` (constants)
- Used by: `Code.gs` (menu actions), `Transacoes.gs` (auto-refresh after save), `Setup.gs` (initial setup)
- Purpose: Google Gemini AI integration for receipt/statement OCR, financial insights, and category suggestion
- Location: `Gemini.gs`
- Contains: `analisarComprovante()` (vision API for image analysis), `obterInsightsMensais()` (text generation for financial advice), `sugerirCategoria()` (auto-categorization), `testarConexaoGemini()`, `chamarGeminiAPI()` (HTTP client), `_repararArrayTruncado()` (JSON repair for truncated responses), `normalizarTiposExtratoGemini()` (post-processing heuristics)
- Depends on: `Configuracoes.gs` (`getGeminiApiKey`, `getTodasConfigs`, `getCategoriasList`, `getMetodosPagamento`), `Transacoes.gs` (transaction data for insights)
- Used by: HTML clients (via `google.script.run`)
- Purpose: Create and configure all Google Sheets tabs with headers, formatting, conditional rules, and default data
- Location: `Setup.gs`
- Contains: `criarEstruturaPlanilha()` (orchestrator), `criarAbaConfig()`, `criarAbaCategorias()`, `criarAbaOrcamento()`, `criarAbaTransacoes()`, `criarAbaPerfil()`, `criarAbaConjunto()`, `criarAbaPoupanca()`, `criarAbaSalarioMes()`, `criarAbaDashboard()`, helpers `getOuCriarAba()`, `estilizarHeader()`
- Depends on: `Configuracoes.gs` (`getConfig`), `Dashboard.gs` (`atualizarDashboard`), `Code.gs` (constants)
- Used by: `Code.gs` (`inicializarPlanilha`), HTML clients (via `criarEstruturaPlanilha`)
- Purpose: Shared formatting and helper functions
- Location: `Utils.gs`
- Contains: `formatarMoeda()`, `formatarData()`, `obterMesAnoAtual()`, `planilhaInicializada()`, `logErro()`
- Depends on: `Configuracoes.gs` (`getConfig`), `Code.gs` (constants)
- Used by: Available globally but primarily used server-side
- Purpose: Full-featured SPA served as standalone web application via `doGet()`
- Location: `WebApp.html`
- Contains: Complete UI with 7 tabs (Dashboard, TransaГ§ГЈo, Extrato, PoupanГ§a, Comprovante, RelatГіrio, Config), Chart.js integration, all client-side state management and rendering logic (~2119 lines)
- Depends on: All server-side functions via `google.script.run` (calls `getDadosIniciais`, `obterDadosRelatorio`, `salvarTransacao`, `salvarMultiplasTransacoes`, `editarTransacao`, `excluirTransacao`, `excluirMultiplasTransacoes`, `listarTransacoes`, `analisarComprovante`, `sugerirCategoria`, `obterInsightsMensais`, `salvarConfiguracoes`, `salvarMetodosPagamento`, `testarConexaoGemini`, `criarEstruturaPlanilha`, `getSaldoPoupanca`, `getPoupanca`, `salvarPoupanca`, `excluirPoupanca`, `getOrcamentos`, `salvarOrcamentos`, `getMesesDisponiveis`)
- Used by: End users accessing the deployed Web App URL
- Purpose: Lightweight UIs embedded as sidebars within Google Sheets
- Location: `Sidebar.html`, `ComprovanteSidebar.html`, `ConfiguracoesUI.html`, `Relatorio.html`
- Contains: Focused single-purpose forms matching a subset of WebApp.html functionality
- Depends on: Server-side functions via `google.script.run`
- Used by: Google Sheets menu actions (opened via `SpreadsheetApp.getUi().showSidebar()`)
## Data Flow
- Server-side: Stateless вЂ” every function call reads fresh data from Google Sheets
- Client-side (`WebApp.html`): Module-level variables (`_d`, `_tPessoa`, `_tTipo`, `_dashRel`, `_rDados`, `_exList`, etc.) hold cached state per session
- No state persistence between page loads on the client
## Key Abstractions
- Purpose: Each Google Sheets tab acts as a database table with fixed column schema
- Examples: `рџ’і TransaГ§Гµes` (13 columns, ID-indexed), `вљ™пёЏ Config` (key-value pairs in 2 columns), `рџ“Ѓ Categorias` (lookup table), `рџ“‹ OrГ§amento` (per-person budget limits), `рџ’° PoupanГ§a` (savings ledger), `рџ’µ SalГЎrio mГЄs` (per-person monthly salary reference)
- Pattern: Row 1 = headers (frozen), data starts at row 2, column indices defined in `COL` constant (`Code.gs`)
- Purpose: Central configuration accessible by all modules
- Examples: `Configuracoes.gs в†’ getConfig('gemini_api_key')`, `getTodasConfigs()` (reads entire sheet once, returns typed object)
- Pattern: Column A = key slug (e.g., `nome_pessoa1`, `salario_pessoa2`), Column B = value. `getTodasConfigs()` caches all keys in one read to avoid N+1 sheet reads.
- Purpose: Consistent API contract between server and client
- Pattern: All mutation functions return `{sucesso: boolean, mensagem: string, ...extras}`. Transaction saves may return `{codigo: 'DUPLICATA', existentes: [...]}` for duplicate handling.
- Purpose: Map various person identifiers (number, name, "Pessoa 1"/"Pessoa 2") to canonical person name
- Examples: `Transacoes.gs в†’ resolverPessoaParaPlanilha()`, `numeroPessoaDeNome()`, `pessoaTransacaoCorrespondeFiltro()`
- Pattern: Accepts `pessoaNum` (1 or 2), raw person name, or legacy "Pessoa 1"/"Pessoa 2" strings; normalizes against `вљ™пёЏ Config` names
- Purpose: Adjust transaction dates based on credit card statement closing date
- Examples: `Transacoes.gs в†’ aplicarCompetenciaCartaoCredito()`, `obterDiaFechamentoCartao()`
- Pattern: If transaction date > closing day and payment method is "CartГЈo de CrГ©dito", competence shifts to 1st of next month. Per-person closing dates supported.
## Entry Points
- Location: `Code.gs` line 38
- Triggers: HTTP GET request to the deployed Web App URL
