## Error Handling
- All server-side public functions wrap logic in try-catch, returning `{sucesso: false, mensagem: e.message}` on failure
- Non-critical operations (dashboard refresh after save, salary config update) are wrapped in nested try-catch with silent catch to prevent cascading failures
- `Logger.log()` used for server-side error logging (visible in Apps Script execution logs)
- Client-side uses `withFailureHandler()` on every `google.script.run` call to display error alerts
- Gemini API responses include JSON repair logic (`_repararArrayTruncado`) and multiple parse attempts with trailing comma cleanup
- `getTodasConfigs()` falls back to `_configDefaults()` if Config sheet is missing or unreadable
